// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//  GAP-09 — multi-file schema: AUTH & TENANCY
//
//  Owns:
//    • Tenant + Organization (hub-and-spoke)
//    • TenantMembership / OrgMembership / TenantCustomRole
//    • User (NextAuth Prisma adapter shape)
//    • Account / Session (NextAuth)
//    • UserSession (Epic C.3 — server-recorded session record with
//      ipAddress/userAgent/expiresAt for revocation)
//    • TenantInviteToken
//    • TenantSecuritySettings
//    • SsoConnection / ScimToken
//
//  Cross-domain relations declared here that point INTO this file:
//    • Every tenant-scoped model has a `tenant Tenant @relation(...)`
//      and a `tenantId String` — declared on the OWNING side
//      (i.e. the model's own domain file). The reverse relation field
//      on Tenant is what lives here.
//
//  Why keep all auth/tenancy together: the back-reference fields on
//  Tenant span every domain (controls, risks, evidence, …). Splitting
//  Tenant out from User/Membership would force every domain file to
//  re-import Tenant relations, scattering the join surface.
//
//  This file is currently empty. The actual auth/tenancy models live
//  in `schema.prisma` and will be relocated here as a focused PR.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
